<sec id="Sec10" class="sec">
 <div class="title" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Surface energy budget and surface temperature</div>
 <p id="Par34" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">The energy budget of the surface layer, or the net-energy transfer 
  <div id="IEq78" class="inline-formula">
   <div class="alternatives">
    <span id="M167" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$${F}_{{\rm{sfc}}}$$\end{document}</span>
    <div id="M168" class="math">
     <div class="msub">
      <div class="mrow">
       <span class="mi">F</span>
      </div>
      <div class="mrow">
       <span mathvariant="normal" class="mi">sfc</span>
      </div>
     </div>
    </div>
    <span xlink:href="41467_2019_11975_Article_IEq78.gif" class="inline-graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
   </div>
  </div> between the atmosphere and the ocean can be written as
  <span class="sup">
   <a ref-type="bibr" rid="CR9" href="#CR9">9</a>,
   <a ref-type="bibr" rid="CR13" href="#CR13">13</a>
  </span>
  <div id="Equ7" class="disp-formula">
   <span class="label">7</span>
   <div class="alternatives">
    <span id="M169" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$${F}_{{\rm{sfc}}}={C}_{{\rm{t}}}\frac{\partial {T}_{{\rm{s}}}}{\partial t}-C=\left(1-{i}_{0}\right)\left(1-\alpha \right){\mathrm{SW}}{\downarrow} +{\mathrm{LW}}{\downarrow} +{\mathrm{LW}}{\uparrow} +Q$$\end{document}</span>
    <div id="M170" class="math">
     <div class="msub">
      <div class="mrow">
       <span class="mi">F</span>
      </div>
      <div class="mrow">
       <span mathvariant="normal" class="mi">sfc</span>
      </div>
     </div>
     <span class="mo">=</span>
     <div class="msub">
      <div class="mrow">
       <span class="mi">C</span>
      </div>
      <div class="mrow">
       <span mathvariant="normal" class="mi">t</span>
      </div>
     </div>
     <div class="mfrac">
      <div class="mrow">
       <span class="mi">∂</span>
       <div class="msub">
        <div class="mrow">
         <span class="mi">T</span>
        </div>
        <div class="mrow">
         <span mathvariant="normal" class="mi">s</span>
        </div>
       </div>
      </div>
      <div class="mrow">
       <span class="mi">∂</span>
       <span class="mi">t</span>
      </div>
     </div>
     <span class="mo">−</span>
     <span class="mi">C</span>
     <span class="mo">=</span>
     <div close=")" open="(" separators="" class="mfenced">
      <div class="mrow">
       <span class="mn">1</span>
       <span class="mo">−</span>
       <div class="msub">
        <div class="mrow">
         <span class="mi">i</span>
        </div>
        <div class="mrow">
         <span class="mn">0</span>
        </div>
       </div>
      </div>
     </div>
     <div close=")" open="(" separators="" class="mfenced">
      <div class="mrow">
       <span class="mn">1</span>
       <span class="mo">−</span>
       <span class="mi">α</span>
      </div>
     </div>
     <span mathvariant="normal" class="mi">SW</span>
     <span class="mi">↓</span>
     <span class="mo">+</span>
     <span mathvariant="normal" class="mi">LW</span>
     <span class="mi">↓</span>
     <span class="mo">+</span>
     <span mathvariant="normal" class="mi">LW</span>
     <span class="mi">↑</span>
     <span class="mo">+</span>
     <span class="mi">Q</span>
    </div>
    <div xlink:href="41467_2019_11975_Article_Equ7.gif" position="anchor" class="graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
   </div>
  </div>where 
  <div id="IEq79" class="inline-formula">
   <div class="alternatives">
    <span id="M171" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$${C}_{{\rm{t}}}$$\end{document}</span>
    <div id="M172" class="math">
     <div class="msub">
      <div class="mrow">
       <span class="mi">C</span>
      </div>
      <div class="mrow">
       <span mathvariant="normal" class="mi">t</span>
      </div>
     </div>
    </div>
    <span xlink:href="41467_2019_11975_Article_IEq79.gif" class="inline-graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
   </div>
  </div> is the thermal resistance of the surface layer, 
  <div id="IEq80" class="inline-formula">
   <div class="alternatives">
    <span id="M173" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$C$$\end{document}</span>
    <div id="M174" class="math">
     <span class="mi">C</span>
    </div>
    <span xlink:href="41467_2019_11975_Article_IEq80.gif" class="inline-graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
   </div>
  </div> is the the conduction of heat from the ocean through the sea-ice/snow to the atmosphere, 
  <div id="IEq81" class="inline-formula">
   <div class="alternatives">
    <span id="M175" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$${i}_{0}$$\end{document}</span>
    <div id="M176" class="math">
     <div class="msub">
      <div class="mrow">
       <span class="mi">i</span>
      </div>
      <div class="mrow">
       <span class="mn">0</span>
      </div>
     </div>
    </div>
    <span xlink:href="41467_2019_11975_Article_IEq81.gif" class="inline-graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
   </div>
  </div> denotes the part of the downwelling shortwave radiation that penetrated through the surface layer, 
  <div id="IEq82" class="inline-formula">
   <div class="alternatives">
    <span id="M177" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$\alpha$$\end{document}</span>
    <div id="M178" class="math">
     <span class="mi">α</span>
    </div>
    <span xlink:href="41467_2019_11975_Article_IEq82.gif" class="inline-graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
   </div>
  </div> is the surface albedo, 
  <div id="IEq83" class="inline-formula">
   <div class="alternatives">
    <span id="M179" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$${\mathrm{SW}}{\downarrow}$$\end{document}</span>
    <div id="M180" class="math">
     <span mathvariant="normal" class="mi">SW</span>
     <span class="mi">↓</span>
    </div>
    <span xlink:href="41467_2019_11975_Article_IEq83.gif" class="inline-graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
   </div>
  </div> is the surface downwelling short-wave radiation flux, LW
  <div id="IEq84" class="inline-formula">
   <div class="alternatives">
    <span id="M181" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$\downarrow$$\end{document}</span>
    <div id="M182" class="math">
     <span class="mi">↓</span>
    </div>
    <span xlink:href="41467_2019_11975_Article_IEq84.gif" class="inline-graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
   </div>
  </div> is the surface downwelling longwave radiation flux, LW
  <div id="IEq85" class="inline-formula">
   <div class="alternatives">
    <span id="M183" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$\uparrow$$\end{document}</span>
    <div id="M184" class="math">
     <span class="mi">↑</span>
    </div>
    <span xlink:href="41467_2019_11975_Article_IEq85.gif" class="inline-graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
   </div>
  </div> is the surface upwelling long-wave radiation flux, 
  <div id="IEq86" class="inline-formula">
   <div class="alternatives">
    <span id="M185" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$Q$$\end{document}</span>
    <div id="M186" class="math">
     <span class="mi">Q</span>
    </div>
    <span xlink:href="41467_2019_11975_Article_IEq86.gif" class="inline-graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
   </div>
  </div> is the turbulent flux of sensible and latent heat. In the polar night conditions the downwelling shortwave radiation flux is very small and could be neglected from the Eq. (
  <a rid="Equ7" ref-type="" href="#Equ7">7</a>). The conductive flux from the ocean to the snow surface is not directly observed. However, we can estimate it as
  <div id="Equ8" class="disp-formula">
   <span class="label">8</span>
   <div class="alternatives">
    <span id="M187" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$C=\frac{{k}_{{\rm{i}}}\cdot {k}_{{\rm{s}}}}{{k}_{{\rm{s}}}\cdot {h}_{{\rm{i}}}+{k}_{{\rm{i}}}\cdot {h}_{{\rm{s}}}}({T}_{{\rm{o}}}-{T}_{{\rm{skin}}})$$\end{document}</span>
    <div id="M188" class="math">
     <span class="mi">C</span>
     <span class="mo">=</span>
     <div class="mfrac">
      <div class="mrow">
       <div class="msub">
        <div class="mrow">
         <span class="mi">k</span>
        </div>
        <div class="mrow">
         <span mathvariant="normal" class="mi">i</span>
        </div>
       </div>
       <span class="mo">⋅</span>
       <div class="msub">
        <div class="mrow">
         <span class="mi">k</span>
        </div>
        <div class="mrow">
         <span mathvariant="normal" class="mi">s</span>
        </div>
       </div>
      </div>
      <div class="mrow">
       <div class="msub">
        <div class="mrow">
         <span class="mi">k</span>
        </div>
        <div class="mrow">
         <span mathvariant="normal" class="mi">s</span>
        </div>
       </div>
       <span class="mo">⋅</span>
       <div class="msub">
        <div class="mrow">
         <span class="mi">h</span>
        </div>
        <div class="mrow">
         <span mathvariant="normal" class="mi">i</span>
        </div>
       </div>
       <span class="mo">+</span>
       <div class="msub">
        <div class="mrow">
         <span class="mi">k</span>
        </div>
        <div class="mrow">
         <span mathvariant="normal" class="mi">i</span>
        </div>
       </div>
       <span class="mo">⋅</span>
       <div class="msub">
        <div class="mrow">
         <span class="mi">h</span>
        </div>
        <div class="mrow">
         <span mathvariant="normal" class="mi">s</span>
        </div>
       </div>
      </div>
     </div>
     <div class="mrow">
      <span class="mo">(</span>
      <div class="mrow">
       <div class="msub">
        <div class="mrow">
         <span class="mi">T</span>
        </div>
        <div class="mrow">
         <span mathvariant="normal" class="mi">o</span>
        </div>
       </div>
       <span class="mo">−</span>
       <div class="msub">
        <div class="mrow">
         <span class="mi">T</span>
        </div>
        <div class="mrow">
         <span mathvariant="normal" class="mi">skin</span>
        </div>
       </div>
      </div>
      <span class="mo">)</span>
     </div>
    </div>
    <div xlink:href="41467_2019_11975_Article_Equ8.gif" position="anchor" class="graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
   </div>
  </div>where 
  <div id="IEq87" class="inline-formula">
   <div class="alternatives">
    <span id="M189" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$${T}_{{\rm{o}}}$$\end{document}</span>
    <div id="M190" class="math">
     <div class="msub">
      <div class="mrow">
       <span class="mi">T</span>
      </div>
      <div class="mrow">
       <span mathvariant="normal" class="mi">o</span>
      </div>
     </div>
    </div>
    <span xlink:href="41467_2019_11975_Article_IEq87.gif" class="inline-graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
   </div>
  </div> is the surface ocean temperature, 
  <div id="IEq88" class="inline-formula">
   <div class="alternatives">
    <span id="M191" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$${k}_{{\rm{s}}}$$\end{document}</span>
    <div id="M192" class="math">
     <div class="msub">
      <div class="mrow">
       <span class="mi">k</span>
      </div>
      <div class="mrow">
       <span mathvariant="normal" class="mi">s</span>
      </div>
     </div>
    </div>
    <span xlink:href="41467_2019_11975_Article_IEq88.gif" class="inline-graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
   </div>
  </div> is the thermal conductivity of snow, and 
  <div id="IEq89" class="inline-formula">
   <div class="alternatives">
    <span id="M193" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$${h}_{{\rm{s}}}$$\end{document}</span>
    <div id="M194" class="math">
     <div class="msub">
      <div class="mrow">
       <span class="mi">h</span>
      </div>
      <div class="mrow">
       <span mathvariant="normal" class="mi">s</span>
      </div>
     </div>
    </div>
    <span xlink:href="41467_2019_11975_Article_IEq89.gif" class="inline-graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
   </div>
  </div> is the thickness of the snow layer on top of sea-ice. For the thermal conductivity of snow and sea-ice we assume, 
  <div id="IEq90" class="inline-formula">
   <div class="alternatives">
    <span id="M195" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$${k}_{{\rm{s}}}=0.31\ {\mathrm{W}}{{\mathrm{m}}}^{-1} \, {{\mathrm{K}}}^{-1}$$\end{document}</span>
    <div id="M196" class="math">
     <div class="msub">
      <div class="mrow">
       <span class="mi">k</span>
      </div>
      <div class="mrow">
       <span mathvariant="normal" class="mi">s</span>
      </div>
     </div>
     <span class="mo">=</span>
     <span class="mn">0.31</span>
     <span width="0.33em" class="mspace"/>
     <span mathvariant="normal" class="mi">W</span>
     <div class="msup">
      <div class="mrow">
       <span mathvariant="normal" class="mi">m</span>
      </div>
      <div class="mrow">
       <span class="mo">−</span>
       <span class="mn">1</span>
      </div>
     </div>
     <span width="0.25em" class="mspace"/>
     <div class="msup">
      <div class="mrow">
       <span mathvariant="normal" class="mi">K</span>
      </div>
      <div class="mrow">
       <span class="mo">−</span>
       <span class="mn">1</span>
      </div>
     </div>
    </div>
    <span xlink:href="41467_2019_11975_Article_IEq90.gif" class="inline-graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
   </div>
  </div> and 
  <div id="IEq91" class="inline-formula">
   <div class="alternatives">
    <span id="M197" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$${k}_{{\rm{i}}}=2.1\ {\mathrm{W}}{{\mathrm{m}}}^{-1} \, {{\mathrm{K}}}^{-1}$$\end{document}</span>
    <div id="M198" class="math">
     <div class="msub">
      <div class="mrow">
       <span class="mi">k</span>
      </div>
      <div class="mrow">
       <span mathvariant="normal" class="mi">i</span>
      </div>
     </div>
     <span class="mo">=</span>
     <span class="mn">2.1</span>
     <span width="0.33em" class="mspace"/>
     <span mathvariant="normal" class="mi">W</span>
     <div class="msup">
      <div class="mrow">
       <span mathvariant="normal" class="mi">m</span>
      </div>
      <div class="mrow">
       <span class="mo">−</span>
       <span class="mn">1</span>
      </div>
     </div>
     <span width="0.25em" class="mspace"/>
     <div class="msup">
      <div class="mrow">
       <span mathvariant="normal" class="mi">K</span>
      </div>
      <div class="mrow">
       <span class="mo">−</span>
       <span class="mn">1</span>
      </div>
     </div>
    </div>
    <span xlink:href="41467_2019_11975_Article_IEq91.gif" class="inline-graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
   </div>
  </div>, respectively. Note that Eq. (
  <a rid="Equ8" ref-type="" href="#Equ8">8</a>) implies steady linear temperature profile within the sea-ice layer. This assumption is not generally correct in case of rapid changes of weather conditions or multilayer sea-ice schemes, especially when snow and ice layers are of considerable thickness. However, taking into account minor variability of weather conditions during a single polar night CSE, Eq. (
  <a rid="Equ8" ref-type="" href="#Equ8">8</a>) could provide a simple first-order estimate of the real conductive heat flux.
 </p>
 <p id="Par35" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">If we assume that a variation 
  <div id="IEq92" class="inline-formula">
   <div class="alternatives">
    <span id="M199" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$\Delta R$$\end{document}</span>
    <div id="M200" class="math">
     <span mathvariant="normal" class="mi">Δ</span>
     <span class="mi">R</span>
    </div>
    <span xlink:href="41467_2019_11975_Article_IEq92.gif" class="inline-graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
   </div>
  </div> in the net longwave radiation budget 
  <div id="IEq93" class="inline-formula">
   <div class="alternatives">
    <span id="M201" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$R={\mathrm{LW}}{\downarrow} +{\mathrm{LW}}{\uparrow}$$\end{document}</span>
    <div id="M202" class="math">
     <span class="mi">R</span>
     <span class="mo">=</span>
     <span mathvariant="normal" class="mi">LW</span>
     <span class="mi">↓</span>
     <span class="mo">+</span>
     <span mathvariant="normal" class="mi">LW</span>
     <span class="mi">↑</span>
    </div>
    <span xlink:href="41467_2019_11975_Article_IEq93.gif" class="inline-graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
   </div>
  </div> balances the changes in the conductive heat flux 
  <div id="IEq94" class="inline-formula">
   <div class="alternatives">
    <span id="M203" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$\Delta C$$\end{document}</span>
    <div id="M204" class="math">
     <span mathvariant="normal" class="mi">Δ</span>
     <span class="mi">C</span>
    </div>
    <span xlink:href="41467_2019_11975_Article_IEq94.gif" class="inline-graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
   </div>
  </div> induced by errors in snow thickness 
  <div id="IEq95" class="inline-formula">
   <div class="alternatives">
    <span id="M205" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$\Delta {h}_{{\rm{s}}}$$\end{document}</span>
    <div id="M206" class="math">
     <span mathvariant="normal" class="mi">Δ</span>
     <div class="msub">
      <div class="mrow">
       <span class="mi">h</span>
      </div>
      <div class="mrow">
       <span mathvariant="normal" class="mi">s</span>
      </div>
     </div>
    </div>
    <span xlink:href="41467_2019_11975_Article_IEq95.gif" class="inline-graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
   </div>
  </div> and sea ice thickness 
  <div id="IEq96" class="inline-formula">
   <div class="alternatives">
    <span id="M207" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$\Delta {h}_{{\rm{i}}}$$\end{document}</span>
    <div id="M208" class="math">
     <span mathvariant="normal" class="mi">Δ</span>
     <div class="msub">
      <div class="mrow">
       <span class="mi">h</span>
      </div>
      <div class="mrow">
       <span mathvariant="normal" class="mi">i</span>
      </div>
     </div>
    </div>
    <span xlink:href="41467_2019_11975_Article_IEq96.gif" class="inline-graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
   </div>
  </div>, we can write 
